<doc id="291230" wikidata="Q731506" url="?curid=291230" title="USS Shaw">
<text>Two United States Navy destroyers have been named USS &quot;Shaw&quot;, after John Shaw, a notable officer in the early days of the Navy.

* , commissioned 1917, decommissioned 1922, transferred to the United States Coast Guard in 1926.
* , commissioned 1936, decommissioned 1945.</text><links>
